fields.description:
I updated the embedded version of Git in SourceTree this morning and am now getting an error dialog about every 10 seconds.  I have attached 2 screen shots to show the Git settings and the error dialog. 

The error is: 
{noformat}
The procedure entry point CONF_modules_load_file could not be located in the dynamic link library LIBEAY32.dll.
{noformat}

This updating of the Git version is the only change I have made recently.

In Sourcetree a diff is shown for changed files. In this diff all dots in the line are replaced by underscores. But the first 2 new lines don't show the underscore while it is there.
Also if I copy and paste the line the underscore comes along with it:
+ map.put("context_path", contextPath);
